revision.text:
'''Christine Roche''' is French Canadian illustrator, cartoonist, and film-maker who lives and works in London.<ref name="Screenonline">[http://www.screenonline.org.uk/film/id/468262/index.html Screenonline]</ref> Her work has appeared in several books, magazines, and national newspapers.

She now paints.

==Biography==
Christine Roche has illustrated many books, both for children and adults, and worked for a number of leading publishers. She has produced animated films for [[Channel 4]] and [[UNICEF]] and lectured in various colleges including the [[London College of Communication]]<ref>[http://www.littleoctopuspublishing.co.uk/publications.php Octopus publishing] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071010111357/http://www.littleoctopuspublishing.co.uk/publications.php |date=2007-10-10 }}</ref>, the [[Royal College of Art]] <ref>[http://www.rca.ac.uk/pages/study/staff_297.html RCA site] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071026001510/http://www.rca.ac.uk/pages/study/staff_297.html |date=2007-10-26 }}</ref> and the National Institute of Design (NID) in India

She is a member of the [[Hackney Flashers]] collective of feminist photographers started in the 1970s.

She is author of ''I'm Not a Feminist But...''(1985) which she made into an animated film with [[Marjut Rimminen]].<ref name="screenonline.org.uk">[http://www.screenonline.org.uk/film/id/791305/index.html Screenonline]</ref>

She also co-directed the short animated films ''The Stain'' (1991) <ref>[[IMDbTitle:0385251|IMDb ''The Stain'']]</ref> viewable at the [https://archive.org/details/TheStainRimminenRoche Internet Archive] and ''Someone Must Be Trusted'' (1987).<ref>[http://www.yadinproductions.com/film_info/Blind_Justice_info.htm Someone Must Be Trusted]</ref>

She designed the characters<ref>[http://www.thefreelibrary.com/CINAR,+BBC+and+HALO+Explore+Teenage+Angst+in+Treasure-YTV+to...-a058526921 Montreal--(Business wire)--Jan. 11, 2000]</ref> in the children's television cartoon series ''[[Treasure (animated television series)|Treasure]]''<ref>[http://www.abc.net.au/abckids/shows/prog172.htm ABC Kids]</ref>

Her work appears in the anthology ''Funny Girls - Cartooning for Equality'' edited by Diane Atkinson (Penguin Books 1997)<ref>[http://www.illustration-agency.com/network/fanny/newdir.htm Illustration Agency]  {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070903074027/http://www.illustration-agency.com/network/fanny/newdir.htm |date=September 3, 2007 }}</ref>

